##My 30 days in the West courtyard of Wuhan Xiehe

Micro-signal Zairenjian11

Features, with a calm narrative against the cold | phoenix network produced in the human studio

Phoenix News Client, produced by Phoenix Network Studio on Earth

I am Beijing Daily photojournalist and Guanxin, on January 27, I followed the Hubei Medical team came to Wuhan, on the battle against new pneumonia battlefield. Yesterday, February 25, was my 30th day in Wuhan.

After the Hubei and Beijing medical teams arrived in Wuhan, they carried out rescue work at the Wuhan Union Hospital. The hospital, the third in Wuhan to admit patients with fever, did not have a specialised ward suitable for such infectious disease. At the end of January and the beginning of February, the hospital welcomed the arrival of 15 provincial and municipal chi-yuan medical teams from Beijing, Heilongjiang and Guangdong, and opened 15 general wards, a maternity ward and an ICU ward with 810 beds.

■ The main entrance of the Wuhan Union Hospital on Jan. 28.

Wuhan Union Hospital is about 20 km from Hankou, Florida, the eye of the new crown pneumonia storm, and about 15 km from Vulcan Mountain Hospital in Caidian District.

After the opening of a new area of pneumonia, here gradually gathered the provincial and municipal elite medical team, as a special hospital to receive critically ill patients.

■ On Feb. 18, ambulances drove to Vulcan Mountain Hospital.

On January 28, the day after I arrived in Wuhan, I joined the Beijing Medical Team at the Wuhan Union Hospital. After the hospital fever clinic, I made a special observation, and there is no network of the kind of long line can not see the disease, also can not be hospitalized. The door to the clinic was quiet, with a few people going in and out, or sitting and waiting on the grass, or standing and hovering at the door.

■ On January 28, there were not many people at the fever clinic of Xiehe West Hospital in Wuhan.

■ workers and citizens wearing masks outside the fever clinic of the Xiehe West Hospital in Wuhan on Jan. 28.

When I spoke to the hospital staff, I learned that there was no room in Wuhan Union Hospital for the treatment of NCP, that patients could not be hospitalized, and that those who needed to be hospitalized had been transferred to other hospitals, only some patients with mild illness travel daily for treatment.

■ On Jan. 28, a girl sat alone on the grass in the corner of the parking lot of a hospital clinic.

With the arrival of provincial and municipal medical teams, many of the general wards in the Wuhan Union Hospital's inpatient building have been temporarily converted into isolation wards. Ward transformation process is very rapid, is basically overnight transformation, closed corridors, open wall holes to do zoning.

According to the hospital in charge of publicity, because Wuhan is closed, all businesses are stopped, renovation ward use of building materials, even from the closed building materials market by acquaintances shipped out of the warehouse.

■ On January 28, health care workers in concord were cleaning up the hepatobiliary and Vascular Surgery Ward and converting it into a new isolated coronary pneumonia ward.

Although the reformed ward is still far from the standard of the professional isolation ward for infectious diseases, it still has the basic admission conditions. This hospital, too, began to be filled with hope for life.

For the next month, I spent almost every day in this hospital, waiting for staff to come in and out of isolation rooms, patients to come and go, and watching the staff in different positions do their part to keep the hospital running.

As the epidemic spread, people struggled to stay alive in this hospital and to fight. I was among them, or just pass by, or had a short time together, with the camera to capture their life segments, ordinary moments and mixed moments.

■ On January 29, the ward under the charge of the Beijing medical team received the first batch of more than 20 patients with new coronavirus pneumonia. As this is a newly opened ward, most of the first patients are not critically ill and can walk out of the ambulance on their own. They carried their belongings and entered the ward on their own or supported.

This was the first time I had ever been in contact with a patient with a new case of Coronopneumonia, and although I was far away, I could still feel their powerlessness, not only physically but also psychologically. They don't know where the strange ward in front of them, and the faceless staff, can take them.

■ On the afternoon of Jan. 29, the first patients received by the Beijing medical team arrived and were helped into the ward by protective medical staff.

As the admission process became smoother and the medical team became more familiar with the ward and ward, the Beijing medical team took charge of the ward and began to mainly admit the critically ill patients.

The medical teams supporting the hospital are all excellent soldiers from many provinces and cities. Receiving the patients with serious illness can save their lives to a greater extent. But the complex conditions in the intensive care unit put the support staff in the busiest and most dangerous position on a daily basis.

■ On Jan. 29, a critically ill patient was wheeled into a hospital ward on a stretcher.

In the three wards under the charge of the Beijing medical team, the Beijing Medical Team members and the medical staff of the local Union hospital are on duty in cooperation. The medical staff from Beijing are all specialized departments related to pneumonia, such as the Department of infection, the Department of aspiration and the Department of emergency treatment, most of Concorde's staff are from other general wards. In the ward, a doctor from Beijing and a doctor from the hospital are on duty for each shift, while nurses are arranged by mixed personnel from both places.

■ nurses at the personal protective equipment gather around a computer to learn how to dress for the occasion on Jan. 28.

The treatment and care of the disease is new to the medical staff of the local hospitals, who come from non-aspiration and non-infection general departments. Scientific and strict prevention and control is the most important thing to isolate the virus, many nurses also learn from virtually nothing about strict protective measures.

■ Liang Xiaohua and Peng Jingdi, nurses at Wuhan Union Hospital, fight side by side in the same new pneumonia ward.

In the face of this unknown danger, the medical staff at Wuhan Union Hospital Did Not Flinch, even if the same hospital double staff, also double on the line.

Wuhan Union Hospital's Nurses, Liang Xiaohua and Peng Jingdi, are a married couple fighting side by side in the same new pneumonia ward. They are post 90s parents of a 7 month old. Because of the new crown pneumonia outbreak, they chose to temporarily leave the family, the children to the care of grandparents, their daily accommodation, to the ward to work.

For them, Wuhan is their home, Wuhan people are their "family. ".

■ Gao Xiuqin speaks to reporters on Feb. 11.

Gao Xiuqin, a 30 year old nurse at Wuhan Union Hospital, had an old lung problem, but she volunteered. Just to the isolation ward, Gao Xiuqin Heart Uneasy, Beijing medical team comrades taught her to do every step of protection, let her slowly relax down.

■ On Jan. 30, a doctor who stepped out of the ward and took off his protective clothing found his clothes soaking wet.

Isolation Ward conditions difficult, two layers of protective clothing isolation clothing, three layers of respirator gloves shoe cover, airtight protection so that everyone is breathing difficulties, blocked sight, sweating.

■ On Jan. 31, a nurse was covered with medical tape after being strangled with a mask over her face.

For a long time wearing mask goggles and other protective equipment, every medical staff out of the ward face almost left a deep ligature marks.

■ On Feb. 8, a nurse at Xuanwu Hospital in Beijing, Ruan Zheng, drew a heart on the top of her protective clothing before entering the ward, with a sign that read "Fighting. ".

In the face of danger, almost everyone enters the isolation ward with a smile. They cheer for each other, cheer for the patients in various ways, and draw warm symbols on their protective clothing, write different words of encouragement for each other.

■ Two nurses help each other put on protective clothing on Feb. 8.

The relationship between the medical staff, and the virus in close contact again and again, again and again after the isolation ward deeper and deeper.

■ A cleaner wears a large garbage bag as a raincoat as he leaves work in the snow on Feb. 15.

A hospital is not run entirely by health care workers, and many basic support jobs, such as cleaning staff, are essential.

ISOLATION WARD CLEANING STAFF DAILY TRANSPORT MEDICAL WASTE, cleaning the ground... to ensure the environmental health of the ward, doing the most basic work. Cleaning staff are not professional medical staff, they continue to stick to their posts, with medical staff into the isolation ward wearing protective clothing, but also muster up a lot of courage. In fact, at the beginning of the ward operation, there have been some cleaning staff reluctant to enter the isolation ward situation. But with the understanding of the protection knowledge, see the personnel in and out of the ward no accident occurred, the logistics personnel's mood also stabilized.

■ On Feb. 15, a security guard wearing a red armband asked two medical workers who had been in and out of the hospital in heavy snow.

Several gates of the Wuhan Union Hospital are guarded 24 hours a day by security personnel, who generally work in the open air, wearing only a mask and wearing no protective clothing because of continuing shortages. Countless health care workers, citizens and even patients pass by every day. They are also the most susceptible people in the hospital, but they still keep working.

■ Yuan Jianhe, a full-body protective ferry driver.

Another indispensable position is the driver of the shuttle bus. There is a distance of about 3 km between the medical team's residence and the hospital, and the local authorities commandeered 579 municipal buses to shuttle medical staff to and from work. Yuan Jianhe of the local bus group is one of the drivers, they are also full body protection in their daily work. Because of close contact with medical staff, so never dare to go home, a month of activity space almost only dormitories and buses.

■ On Feb. 15, during a snowstorm in Wuhan, Beijing Medical Team members braved the wind and snow to go to work at a hospital.

At the turn of winter and spring in Wuhan, the temperature fluctuated, warm up can only wear short-sleeved t-shirt, cold down jacket is not warm enough. The medics have also experienced some extreme weather here.

■ heavy fog on February 22, with minimum visibility of just a few tens of meters.

The new coronary ward will be like a machine to cure the sick and save the sick. As long as there are patients on the bed, the operation will not stop.

■ On Feb. 17, two passers-by passed each other in the hospital and looked back at each other.

For more than a month after the city was shut down, the designated hospital in Wuhan became the center of life for many people, not just medical staff, but even ordinary citizens, sometimes passing each other in the hospital, perhaps even familiar friends.

■ On Feb. 17, an elderly couple, both hospitalized, helped each other to the relevant department for a CT scan.

Being in an isolation ward can mean a separation from a loved one, perhaps even death. It is both unfortunate and fortunate to have a family member in the hospital at the same time as the Wuhan Union Hospital.

Beijing medical team in charge of the ward there is such an elderly couple, are in their eighties. They were not admitted at the same time. They were not in the same room at first, and when the staff learned of the situation, they let the two of them go in and out of the isolation ward each time they took the patient out for a checkup (the CT scan was in another building) . They insist on going back and forth on their own rather than being helped by medical staff. A crippled old man hobbled along on crutches, and the grandmother carefully helped her husband. It's a sad sight.

■ On February 17, security personnel with shields guarded the entrance to the ward to block family members who wanted to enter the ward.

As the number of in-patients increases, the number of family members of patients who stay outside the ward and do not want to leave is increasing. Security Guards in protective suits had to pick up shields and forks to prevent unauthorized access. Many family members do not understand this, they would rather risk their lives, but also for the chance to meet their loved ones.

■ On Feb. 7, doctors from the Beijing medical team shook hands with a discharged patient to congratulate her on her recovery.

Xia was admitted to the hospital with symptoms of cough, fever, and CT features of pneumonia, but the two nucleic acid tests were negative after admission. According to the fifth edition of the COVID-19, these suspected cases in Hubei Province with imaging features of pneumonia are clinically diagnosed.

February 7, the Beijing Medical Team Ward after many days of treatment and care, finally cured discharge, she also became the Beijing medical team ward the first discharge of patients. The medical staff of Ward is very excited, tell Xia Madam"after going out must take care of health, you are the first one that we discharge here, it is our hope!"

■ On Feb. 13, a recovering patient, Ms. Shen, began to dance excitedly.

Then came the good news. Almost every day, patients were discharged from the ward. Ms. Shen, 57, developed symptoms in late January and was sent here. In the hospital treatment, she actively cooperate with optimistic mood treatment, the condition quickly from severe to mild. On February 13, the day she left the hospital, she couldn't help but dance as she walked out of the room. After returning to the community from the hospital to Self-quarantine, Ms. Shen also through wechat group with patients in the ward to encourage them to actively cooperate with treatment.

■ On Feb. 13, patients saw a doctor walk by, hands clasped in the distance.

On Feb. 13, Mr. Chen, who was leaving the ward for a physical examination, stopped on his way back to the ward to greet the doctor, and clasped his hands in gratitude from across the road.

■ A group photo of the discharged patient with the medical staff.

As of 9:00 am on February 25, the Beijing medical team has treated 257 patients in three wards, most of whom were critically ill. A total of 43 cases were discharged, 25 cases were transferred to other wards and 19 cases were transferred to other hospitals. At present, 136 patients are in hospital, including 110 confirmed cases, 26 suspected cases, 112 severe cases, 19 critical cases.

The hospital is like a life-and-death field. Under the epidemic situation, ordinary people come and go. They are mostly nameless, go to stay silent, but each to live, better to live, persist, try hard..

The epidemic is not over. The story is not over. Let them go on with me.

There is a distance of about 3 km between the medical team's residence and the hospital, and the local authorities commandeered 579 municipal buses to shuttle medical staff to and from work. Yuan Jianhe of the local bus group is one of the drivers, they are also full body protection in their daily work. Because of close contact with medical staff, so never dare to go home, a month of activity space almost only dormitories and buses.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
■ On Feb. 15, during a snowstorm in Wuhan, Beijing Medical Team members braved the wind and snow to go to work at a hospital.

At the turn of winter and spring in Wuhan, the temperature fluctuated, warm up can only wear short-sleeved t-shirt, cold down jacket is not warm enough. The medics have also experienced some extreme weather here.

■ On Feb. 17, two passers-by passed each other in the hospital and looked back at each other.

For more than a month after the city was shut down, the designated hospital in Wuhan became the center of life for many people, not just medical staff, but even ordinary citizens, sometimes passing each other in the hospital, perhaps even familiar friends.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
■ On Feb. 17, an elderly couple, both hospitalized, helped each other to the relevant department for a CT scan.

Being in an isolation ward can mean a separation from a loved one, perhaps even death. It is both unfortunate and fortunate to have a family member in the hospital at the same time as the Wuhan Union Hospital.

Beijing medical team in charge of the ward there is such an elderly couple, are in their eighties. They were not admitted at the same time. They were not in the same room at first, and when the staff learned of the situation, they let the two of them go in and out of the isolation ward each time they took the patient out for a checkup (the CT scan was in another building) . They insist on going back and forth on their own rather than being helped by medical staff. A crippled old man hobbled along on crutches, and the grandmother carefully helped her husband. It's a sad sight.

■ On February 17, security personnel with shields guarded the entrance to the ward to block family members who wanted to enter the ward.

As the number of in-patients increases, the number of family members of patients who stay outside the ward and do not want to leave is increasing. Security Guards in protective suits had to pick up shields and forks to prevent unauthorized access. Many family members do not understand this, they would rather risk their lives, but also for the chance to meet their loved ones.

■ On Feb. 7, doctors from the Beijing medical team shook hands with a discharged patient to congratulate her on her recovery.

Xia was admitted to the hospital with symptoms of cough, fever, and CT features of pneumonia, but the two nucleic acid tests were negative after admission. According to the fifth edition of the COVID-19, these suspected cases in Hubei Province with imaging features of pneumonia are clinically diagnosed.

February 7, the Beijing Medical Team Ward after many days of treatment and care, finally cured discharge, she also became the Beijing medical team ward the first discharge of patients. The medical staff of Ward is very excited, tell Xia Madam"after going out must take care of health, you are the first one that we discharge here, it is our hope!"

■ On Feb. 13, a recovering patient, Ms. Shen, began to dance excitedly.

Then came the good news. Almost every day, patients were discharged from the ward. Ms. Shen, 57, developed symptoms in late January and was sent here. In the hospital treatment, she actively cooperate with optimistic mood treatment, the condition quickly from severe to mild. On February 13, the day she left the hospital, she couldn't help but dance as she walked out of the room. After returning to the community from the hospital to Self-quarantine, Ms. Shen also through wechat group with patients in the ward to encourage them to actively cooperate with treatment.

■ A group photo of the discharged patient with the medical staff.

As of 9:00 am on February 25, the Beijing medical team has treated 257 patients in three wards, most of whom were critically ill. A total of 43 cases were discharged, 25 cases were transferred to other wards and 19 cases were transferred to other hospitals. At present, 136 patients are in hospital, including 110 confirmed cases, 26 suspected cases, 112 severe cases, 19 critical cases.

The hospital is like a life-and-death field. Under the epidemic situation, ordinary people come and go. They are mostly nameless, go to stay silent, but each to live, better to live, persist, try hard..

The epidemic is not over. The story is not over. Let them go on with me.
